  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Use case: as Kubernetes admin I want to define a StorageClass that provisions PVs with `PersistentVolumeReclaimPolicy = \"Retain\"` so users don't loose their data when they accidentally delete their PVCs.\r\n\r\n**API changes:**\r\n\r\n* Either \"magic\" annotation `kubernetes.io/reclaim-policy: Retain`\r\n* Or a new StorageClass field `sc.PersistentVolumeReclaimPolicy: Retain`\r\n\r\n**Requested actions:**\r\n\r\n* Update the API.\r\n* Update internal provisioning logic to respect this new annotation/field.\r\n* Update docs.\r\n* Announce that external provisioners need to respect this new annotation/field.\r\n\r\nAll these items are fairly easy if we agree on the design.\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-storage ",
